<item>
            <title>[LU-18741] Alternative Names Policy interface names</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18741</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lnetctl doesn&apos;t recognize alternative names like regular linux commands. This is available since Rocky 8.5 and newer&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ip link show&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211; eth1; .... altname enp0s8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ip link show enp0s8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8212; eth1: ... altname enp0s8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lnetctl net add --net tcp0 --if enp0s8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;add: - net: errno: -1 descr: &quot;couldn&apos;t query intf enp0s8&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Rocky 8.5 and higher</environment>
